<time>1487405648730< /time>< Rating>

< Review>
The first time I went there it was because of an ad I saw in the baldwin park newsletter. My partner and I tried a donut with a nutella mousse in the middle. We could tell straight away that it was not actually nutella but rather some sort of powdery cocoa like nesquik. Did not like at all.

We gave it a second chance the other day, and this convinced us to never go back. We bought a different nutella donut d'crav and a strawberry cream cheese. The cream cheese did not taste like cream cheese at all. The more expensive d'crav advertised to contain nutella did not contain even a hint of it. We asked the woman there if the d'crav had nutella since that was part of its name. She replied in the affirmative, but once we tasted it we could immediately tell that the "nutella" was actually the cheap chocolate crap they put on their basic donuts. That wasn't even the worst part! Not only were the pastries not as described, but the cashier overcharged us for our order! The two pastries were 1.95 and 3.25 respectively, and the order came out to 7.66! We stood outside in the rain contemplating our receipt, and then we went in to ask about the price. The cashier gave us a confused look and checked on a separate register. She told us it was not the right price and tried to refund the credit card. When she did that she so happened to come upon an error where our receipt from nine minutes ago did not show up. Finally, she said her machine was "stuck" and that she couldn't refund the credit card because she couldn't find the receipt that we handed to her. How does that even happen? How did she even overcharge us to begin with? The difference in price was $2.44 and somehow she made the mistake of overcharging us by around %40 of the actual price. We got our refund in cash and left with a feeling that we had been robbed and misled. Not a good business at all!

If you want to get overcharged and have your receipts mysteriously disappear, Tony's will happily oblige. We plan on filing a complaint with our credit card company.<//Review>

The whole job took about 30 minutes.  I also asked him to look at the other toilet in the house as well and ensure that it was working properly, and did not need any repairs.  Steven indicated that it was working fine and didn't need any repairs.  I appreciated him not "upselling me" to unnecessary repairs. <text>Edit to my review: Mr. Yost called me, apologized, asked me what he could do to make things right, and offered to send me a 100% refund. He clearly cares about serving his customers well, and he felt bad that I wasn't happy. Honesty like that is hard to come by these days, and I appreciate him standing behind his work.

Original review: Unfortunately I have to report a pretty negative experience with Yost Appliance Repair. My front-loading washer wouldn't drain, and Mr. Yost (and his son) came out to take a look. They told me that the pump was ruined, it would cost >$400 to fix because they have to take the whole washer apart, and it would probably re-clog with whatever got in it in the first place. They also went on a tirade about how front-loaders are less efficient, unreliable, can't be fixed, and are being foisted on us by "the Europeans". They charged me for a service call, which is fair, and left. So then I went online, and everything I can find disagrees with their assessment of front-loaders. I also found some YouTube videos showing how I could access the pump through a window in the bottom. I didn't even need to take it out; by running the washer a few times, and wiggling the rubber piece that feeds into the pump, I was able to get the pump to clear the jam. It is now working reliably again.

I'm giving them 2 stars instead of 1, because (1) they came out quickly, and (2) they tried running the washer a couple times before deciding it was broken, which helped me figure out how I might be able to get it working by myself.< /text>< Gmap_id>

< text>
Update 6/6/18: Mr. Yost called me yesterday after reading this review to apologize for missing the appointment and to do what he could to make things right. I appreciate that he really does care about his customers and that he does want to provide them with the best service possible.
_____________
Won't be using them again. I went with Yost this time because of all the positive reviews on Google, so I was fairly surprised all of the hassle involved in getting an appointment and getting my fridge ice maker replaced. The first couple times I called, I got their answering machine and left a message. Finally got a hold of the receptionist and gave her my fridge model number to confirm they could do the repairs. She said they do work on that model, but for some reason I had to speak with Mr. Yost before I could actually schedule the appointment. She said he'd call me before the end of the day, but he didn't call that day or the next. I called back the following day and had to give all the information to the receptionist again. Fortunately Mr. Yost was there, but I had to give all the same information to him as well. It's like the receptionist and Mr. Yost weren't communicating.
Finally was able to schedule an appointment and two guys came over to look at my ice maker. Spent less than 5 minutes looking at it, saw that it was bad, and said it needed replacing. They checked their shop, didn't have the part in stock, said they had to order the part, and that they would come by at the same time 2 days later to install it. Great! I was glad it was being taken care of so quickly. Well 2 days later, I'm at my house waiting for them and they missed the appointment. I called their office, but no one picks up. I call Mr. Yost's cell phone and he says he doesn't have the appointment on his schedule. I call the office again and the receptionist said the part isn't in and that they won't be able to install it until the following week. WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE IF THEY LET ME KNOW THEY WOULDN'T BE SHOWING UP TO THE APPOINTMENT!
The same guys show up the following week and spent about 20 minutes removing the old part and installing the new one. Technical Charges were $145, which seems like a lot to me. I know they're specialists, but, in total, the repair guys were probably in my house for less than 30 minutes, and I doubt that looking up the part number and placing the order takes a ton of time or effort. So approximately $290 per hour? I was hoping they would at least have given me some sort of discount for not showing up to an appointment. New ice maker seems to be working fine though.<//text>

<user>115355322614324782721<//user><resp>None</resp><gmap_id>0x809a3135e2c13a3f:0x17315788dbde734b<//gmap_id><review>Beautiful campground, beautiful view, beautiful lake, just wish I could say the same of the people. Since it is free you get some of the "free people" that have no regard for others around them-loud music, rude and want to fight. These are the weekend people.  Come in Monday or Sunday night and head out Friday.  Some folks there were wonderful people,  it only takes one group.  One thing there is cell service and the Sheriff's department responds fast for being in the boonies. Again this is a beautiful area, nice camp sites but avoid the weekend.  Also, the last mile is a dirt road that is passable, we took our 25ft trailer in and saw a couple that were larger.  The lower section is very tight, so becareful with larger rigs. Nicely decorated, good food but a little put off with slightly cold reception when my party first arrived.  Felt host was more concerned with Caucasian patrons than us (minority).  Waiter was a little abrupt when we tried to give him a count of how many cups of coffee we wanted, he preferred to count for himself.  The thing is, the whole restaurant experience also includes the type of service you get from the employee/owner. It's always nice when the host greets you warmly. So these comments have nothing to do with the food. The three stars reflex the attitudes of the employees.  For $76 a person serving 6 people, they should be nicer.< /Review>

< Text>
An out-of-the-way gem!  Tables far enough apart that you don't feel like you're at a baseball game.  Unusual menu items such as octopus (luscious!) and baccala (as good as the maitre d's grandmother used to make it).  An array of pasta dishes to suit a wide range of tastes.  Recommend the panna cotta and apple pastry dessert (similar to tarte tatin).  Modest-sized portions.  Professional, unobtrusive service.  An oasis in the urban bustle.<//Text>

< Review>
this place has the touch of style provided by tall walls and high ceilings with a great attention to style and they're the core. Very classy use of wood Marvel and Inca the core also with mirrors hanging to make you feel on a bigger space than it actually is. The servers are very attentive and always available. The food is tasty and the portion size are  abundant. the price you're going to pay of course it's a little higher which is understandable as they do take care of standing out from the Rest by being more classy it's more attention to clean the nest and presentation. this last time I was there I had the chupe de camaron. A very tasty soup although I was tripping for something else that I saw somebody else having but didn't have the name. I had the mixed ceviche which is a must whenever you go to a Peruvian restaurant. I've had three other favorite restaurants and this is not up to par with them. But I have to say is good enough.</Review>

<review>I came here for lunch with my coworker. I've been driving by this place for months and never knew what was inside. The windows are covered from the outside so I couldn't see what was inside.

What We Ordered:
- Ox Tail Fettuccine
- Chaufa Especial

I love the sauces they provide with your bread. I don't know what they are but, they sure are good. I tried both dishes and they were delicious!! I did feel like my Ox Tail Fettuccine was TOO cheesy. I never thought that was possible. I LOVE cheese. Maybe I felt that it overpowered the oxtail to much. However, with a little hot sauce, it made it taste WAYYYYY better! I think it was even better the next day when I had it for leftovers! The Chaufa Especial was delicious as well! My friend just wished the shrimps had their tails removed. I didn't mind though. I will definitely come back!</review>< pics>

<Pics>None</Pics><review>Quite nice.< /review></record></dataset><record>
<review>I've always been curious about this place because it was on my daily route to work. I've been told it was a really great place so I finally decided to take the plunge. I was about to get a seat for two rather quickly. I did go on a Monday afternoon so the wait was non existent but I can only imagine what it looks like over the weekend.

The first dish brought to us was a plate of dinner rolls with butter and two dipping sauces. One was a creamy green cilantro sauce that had a really nice flavorful kick too it while the other was some kind of orange sauce. I'm not sure what it was but it was a nice contrast to the other sauce.

We then ordered a plate if fried plantains. It was very delicious. We ended up using the butter from the rolls to coat our plantains with just a little more flavor. Not necessary as the flavor was spot on. It was just a little more kick.

We received our two min dishes rather quickly. We had ordered Peruvian fried rice and the lamp shank.

The fried rice had a mix of beek, pork, and shrimp. From the small sample I had it tasted good. Fried rice is fried rice and it's really hard to mess that up.

The lamb shank was so tender. The meat just slid right off the bone. Either it was cooking all day or they have one hell of a pressure cooker. It was served with a scoop if rice along with beans in a soupy sauce. I loved it so much I practically cleared my plate.

I definitely will be coming back. The menu has so many other interesting dishes that look delicious. This is a wonderful restaurant.<//review><Name>John Ross Gatlin</Name>< Response>
None</Response>

< UserId.>
109692583372821212551<//UserId.>
< username>
Saptarshi</username>
< date>
1438239653784</date>
<rate>5<//rate>< text>
We dined at El Rocoto last night and our experience was excellent! It was a Tuesday night but we had to wait for about fifteen minutes - I didn't mind - a crowded restaurant is a good restaurant. I can wait for good things. We ordered Coke and Inka Cola (I like its cough syrupy flavour). While we savoured the complimentary bread rolls with butter and the dips we waited for our orders - Chaufa Especial (Oriental peruvian fried rice with of shrimp, pork, chicken and beef), and Seco Cordero (Braised lamb shank in cilantro sauce with peruvian beans and rice). The orders arrived after a wait of about fifteen minutes - not bad. The fried rice was very good with plenty of meat, and shrimps with a side of sweet and cool radish slices. The braised lamb shank was juicy, soft and literally falling of the bone, with a side of plain rice, white beans and onions freshly pickled with lemon juice. It was exceptional. The portions were big - we had to pack some of the food to take home. The lady serving us was Latin American - she was very polite and accomodating. She even served us a complimentary caramel custard because it took a little longer for our food to arrive.

I would highly recommend the place. It is as good as El Pollo Inka if not better. Their kitchen closes at 9:30 PM, so get there early.</text>
